item.title: Dev Section for MoparRSC
item.dc:creator: @CodeForFame CodeForFame
item.description:
@CodeForFame wrote:

[quote=“Mental Piracy, post:32, topic:394785”][quote author=CodeForFame link=topic=491967.msg3598571#msg3598571 date=1305347796]

More people care about how close the server is to being out than they do about your hidden boards… why not make a post about that.

There is…
https://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,490361.0.html

Yet nothings been checked off or updated, my point still stands, or has nothing been done?

Nothing on that checklist has been done, as far as I’m aware…

I’m also waiting on getting a client of some kind (preferably a ‘fresh’ deob that’s been refactored a bit, but RSCA would be easier) for some other things that need to be done.

You can also check the progress yourself on the GitHub project.
[/quote]
Server progress isnt what im concerned with, getting the server up is, a days worth of work is on that checklist yet its been weeks.

As for the client, a fresh deob is the way to go, rsca’s client is like the source, full of redundancies due to multiple devs and no communication.[/quote]

There is a bit more than a days worth of work, for one person at least… The checklist is simplified, and lacking some things. But ATM it seems like no one is actually doing anything that moves it closer to release.

Read full topic
